
[1]mina

   MI'NA, n. [L. mina.] A weight or denomination of money. The mina of the
   Old Testament was valued at sixty shekels. The Greek or Attic mina, was
   valued at a hundred drachmas, about f2. l7s.sterling, $10.44 cents.
